REVENANT SLEUTH — CHARACTER WEB (Knowledge & Leverage Timeline)
This is who knows what, when, and what power they hold.
Key: Knowledge Flags
K0: Drug = weird, causes violence/undead-like events.
K1: Drug distribution tied to Velvet Abyss.
K2: Symbols + bass patterns influence behavior (obedience mechanism).
K3: Drug is “alive” (heat theft), not normal chemistry.
K4: Max is directly connected to supply chain.
K5: Drug is essence of an ancient Lich Lord; Max resurrected it; army plan.
Kane
Starts with: K0
Gains: K1 (Ch 1), K2 (Ch 4), K3 (Ch 4–5), K4 (Ch 6), K5 (Ch 11)
Leverage: Badge/reputation early; later evidence + personal knowledge of Max.
Evelyn
Starts with: K0/K1 (via Kane)
Gains: K2 (Ch 3–4), K3 sensory (Ch 4–5), K4 (Ch 6–7), K5 (Ch 11)
Leverage: Reads power structures; becomes “sensor” for symbols/bass.
Max
Starts with: K3 (he knows essence behaves strangely) + partial K5 (he knows he resurrected something, but misunderstands its intentions)
Believes: “I’m in control.”
Blind spot: True K5 intent (army + Max as pawn).
Leverage: Network, resources, insider knowledge of Kane.
Voss
Starts with: K1/K2 operationally (he knows the club is part of a system)
May suspect K3 (cold behavior) but frames it as “product quirk.”
Does not necessarily know full K5 (or knows only fragments); he’s a node, not architect.
Leverage: Surveillance, security, political protection.
Lt. Grant
Starts with: departmental narrative (“drug panic,” K0 only)
Gains: K1–K2 gradually if Kane provides proof (Ch 5–8).
Function: gatekeeper; can burn or save Kane’s career.
Dr. Cho
Starts with: K0 via bodies
Gains: K3 via lab anomalies (Ch 5).
Function: credibility; confirms the impossible carefully.
The Lich Lord
Has: full K5 always.
Exerts influence indirectly through: cold, obedience, mirror, scheduling.

Relationship Tension Map (Quick Use)
Kane ↔ Evelyn: trust builds through shared risk + honest backstory exchange; conflict when Kane tries to control plans.
Kane ↔ Max: personal war; each knows the other’s methods; guilt fuels obsession.
Evelyn ↔ Institution: deep mistrust due to witness death; major trigger when Kane faces suspension.
Voss ↔ Max: business relationship with hidden coercion; Voss increasingly resentful.
All ↔ Lich: unknown hand tightening threads; presence felt before understood.

Optional Epilogue/Vacation Constraint (to keep noir bite)
Even on vacation, include one small, unsettling carryover (not a cliffhanger, a bruise):
Kane’s thigh still goes numb in the cold,
Evelyn hears a bass-like rhythm in a distant club,
a news blurb about “unexplained violence” in another city.
This preserves tone while still giving readers emotional release.



